    <!-- FAQ -->
    <section class="faq-section">
        <div class="faq-inner">
            <h2 class="section-title">Frequently Asked <span>Questions</span></h2>
            <div class="section-underline"></div>
            <div class="faq-list">

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
                        <span>What is the minimum amount I need to open a savings account?</span>
                        <i class="fa-solid fa-plus"></i>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>You can open an Easy Saver account with as little as $10. The Goal Saver requires a minimum of $100 and the Fixed Term account requires a minimum opening deposit of $500.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
                        <span>How is interest calculated on my savings?</span>
                        <i class="fa-solid fa-plus"></i>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Interest is calculated daily on your account balance and credited to your account at the end of each month. This means your interest starts working for you from the very first day you deposit.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
                        <span>Can I withdraw my money at any time?</span>
                        <i class="fa-solid fa-plus"></i>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Easy Saver and Goal Saver accounts offer instant access with no withdrawal penalties. The Fixed Term account requires funds to remain deposited for the agreed term to receive the full interest rate.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
                        <span>Are my savings protected?</span>
                        <i class="fa-solid fa-plus"></i>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Yes. All NovaTrust Bank savings accounts are FDIC insured up to $250,000 per depositor. Your money is completely safe with us at all times.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <div class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
                        <span>Can I have more than one savings account?</span>
                        <i class="fa-solid fa-plus"></i>
                    </div>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Yes. You can open multiple savings accounts with NovaTrust Bank to save for different goals at the same time. For example you could have an Easy Saver for emergencies and a Fixed Term account for long-term growth.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

